=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">an open letter to shareh=
olders that Nam Tai filed today</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16p=
x 0;">Dear Shareholders,</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We want to update =
you on our path to securing total on-shore control of Nam Tai Property Inc.=
 (=E2=80=9CNam Tai=E2=80=9D or the =E2=80=9CCompany=E2=80=9D) and its asset=
s. In recent weeks, Jiabiao Wang, whom we believe to be a longtime ally of =
Kaisa Group Holdings Limited (collectively with its affiliates, =E2=80=9CKa=
isa Group=E2=80=9D) and whom the reconstituted Board of Directors (the =E2=
=80=9CBoard=E2=80=9D) has terminated from any role at Nam Tai, has obstruct=
ed an orderly handover of business assets in mainland China. ...</p><p styl=
e=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In direct contravention of the elected Board=E2=80=99=
s decisions and in what appears to be a flagrant violation of the law, Mr. =
Wang =E2=80=93 evidently a long-time ally of Kaisa Group =E2=80=93 is refus=
ing to acknowledge his formal termination and facilitate an orderly handove=
r of the on-shore business despite multiple visits and demands by the Board=
=E2=80=99s recently-appointed legal representative and the new management o=
f the Company. Mr. Wang is currently preventing the new Board from accessin=
g the Company=E2=80=99s and its subsidiaries=E2=80=99 business licenses, co=
rporate seals (also known as chops) and several bank accounts. We believe M=
r. Wang and Kaisa Group are also responsible for the following:</p><p style=
